<HL>
   Armco Modifies Notes Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
09/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C18
</SO>
<CO>
   AS
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   PARSIPPANY, N.J. -- Armco Inc. said it has modified its
consent solicitation and offer to purchase its 13 1/2% senior
notes due 1994 from consenting noteholders.
   The modification increases the consent fee to $17.50 from
$10 for each $1,000 principal amount and extends the offer to
5:01 p.m., EST, Friday, Sept. 28.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Armco wants noteholders to approve an amendment that
allows the company to continue paying common stock dividends.
The steelmaker needs 50.1% of the outstanding $164 million in
notes to approve the change and had about $53.5 million as of
Sept. 17.
</TEXT>
